I need to identify the capital contributed by shareholders in this balance sheet.

Looking at the balance sheet, I need to find the line item that represents the capital contributed by shareholders in exchange for shares.

Typically, this would be represented by the "Paid-in Capital" line item, which shows the amount of capital that shareholders have invested in the company by purchasing shares.

In the balance sheet:
- The "Paid-in Capital" has an initial value of 13000000.00 on 2023-12-31
- The "Paid-in Capital" has an end value of 13000000.00 on 2024-01-29

This represents the capital that shareholders have contributed to the company, and it has remained unchanged during this period.
